The paper discusses the challenges of evaluating and explaining AI-based software, particularly in the context of public sector decision-making. This suggests a focus on AI (cs.AI) and its application in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the sociotechnical aspects of AI, which could fall under the category of complex systems (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes strategies for promoting the adoption of AI in the public sector, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
